parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wheel studs can cause the wheels to detach from the vehicle, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
The failure of the transfer case can cause loss of control, accidents, and even fires, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
The unintended movement of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle rolls away on an incline.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls away while parked
the vehicle moves forward or backward despite being in park
the parking brake must be engaged to prevent movement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration and shaking of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and discomfort for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or vibrates while driving
the vibration is felt through the steering wheel or seat

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Steering and Brake Failure due to High Pressure Booster Hose Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high-pressure booster hose can cause loss of power steering and power brakes, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
The misalignment of the axle and leaning of the frame can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: frame is leaning to one side

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Instability and Swaying at High Speeds
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of steering responsiveness and swaying of the vehicle at high speeds can cause accidents, especially when other vehicles are traveling at higher speeds.
symptoms: Vehicle sways from side to side at high speeds
steering catches suddenly and swaying worsens
